  <span id="freeText15017690234952691990" style="display:none">Ces distances infinites des espace m'effraie. (I quote from (bad) memory. Corrected:<br />"Le silence éternel de ces espaces infinis m'effraie." Even better, since I'm a musician, wrote a book on bird vocalization, Birdtalk, where the European Blackbirds, the Orioles, Robins, the Titmouses and Chickadees (a form of Titmouse, which Emerson's poem of that name admires). I spoke on it 80 times, including once in Milano in Italian, a couple times in the UK. Later I wrote two books on space-man Giordano Bruno, for whom infinite space and its objects imply what NASA spends 20 billion per annum searching for, habitable worlds, for Bruno an infinite number. Google "Giordano Bruno Harvard Video" for my talk at Harvard center for Astrophysics.</span>
