        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer30838338" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11481024092345718630">The Wager is laughably ridiculous and what&apos;s even more ridiculous is that it&apos;s <i>still</i> the standard last ditch move of theological apologetics. Another embarassingly naive thing I remember this otherwise brilliant mathematician and natural philosopher actually preserving with his pen for us to read centuries later was that Christianity is the oldest religion and therefore the best and truest hypothesis concerning questions of god and religion. How many false statements can we extrapolate from this</span>
  <span id="freeText11481024092345718630" style="display:none">The Wager is laughably ridiculous and what's even more ridiculous is that it's <i>still</i> the standard last ditch move of theological apologetics. Another embarassingly naive thing I remember this otherwise brilliant mathematician and natural philosopher actually preserving with his pen for us to read centuries later was that Christianity is the oldest religion and therefore the best and truest hypothesis concerning questions of god and religion. How many false statements can we extrapolate from this...? </span>
